            <div class="comment-body"><p>Not only that, but if he does go for a jury trial, a high number of charges almost guarantees a conviction; jurors want to appear fair, so when the case isn't clearcut, they tend to find guilt on a few of the least serious charges, regardless of the particular evidence for each, so as to not let the guy off scot-free.</p></div>
